        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 6:43AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 640 AM EDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line from near Reese to Lapeer to near Oxford extending west across
the Flint metro area to Owosso. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds near 40 mph and half inch hail. Heavy rainfall along
the I-69 corridor.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs. Minor damage to
outdoor objects is possible. Localized flooding possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Lapeer, Oxford, Vassar, Millington, Columbiaville, Otisville,
Metamora, and Otter Lake around 645 AM EDT.
Rochester around 650 AM EDT.
Dryden around 700 AM EDT.
Romeo around 705 AM EDT.
Imlay City, Almont, Macomb Township, and Lum around 710 AM EDT.
Mayville, Sterling Heights, and Clinton around 715 AM EDT.
Mount Clemens and North Branch around 720 AM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Goodland Township,
Waterford, Arthur, Rankin, Shelby Township, Holly State Recreation
Area, Ray Center, Rose Center, Gera, and Utica.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
